"be efficiently implemented.Notably, our fine-grained quantization strategy is highly consistent with the idea of mi- croscaling formats (Rouhani et al.,2023b), while the Tensor Cores of NVIDIA next-generation GPUs (Blackwell series) have announced the support for microscaling formats with smaller quantization granularity (NVIDIA, 2024a).We hope our design can serve as a reference for future work to keep pace with the latest GPU architectures.Increasing Accumulation Precision.Low-precision GEMM operations often suffer from un- derflow issues, and their accuracy largely depends on high-precision accumulation, which is commonly performed in an FP32 precision (Kalamkar et al.,2019; Narang et al.,2017).However, we observe that the accumulation precision of FP8 GEMM on NVIDIA H800 GPUs is limited to retaining around 14 bits, which is significantly lower than FP32 accumulation precision.This problem will become more pronounced when the inner dimension K is large (Wortsman et al.,",137,987,246,10,17,"[-8.14418588e-03  1.23793157e-02 -1.22721568e-02  1.04598450e-02
