"During training, each single sequence is packed from multiple samples.However, we adopt a sample masking strategy to ensure that these examples remain isolated and mutually invisible.5.2.Reinforcement Learning 5.2.1.Reward Model We employ a rule-based Reward Model (RM) and a model-based RM in our RL process.Rule-Based RM.For questions that can be validated using specific rules, we adopt a rule- based reward system to determine the feedback.For instance, certain math problems have deterministic results, and we require the model to provide the final answer within a designated format (e.g., in a box), allowing us to apply rules to verify the correctness.Similarly, for LeetCode problems, we can utilize a compiler to generate feedback based on test cases.By leveraging rule-based validation wherever possible, we ensure a higher level of reliability, as this approach is resistant to manipulation or exploitation.",134,918,229,10,29,"[-1.47092506e-01  7.58155137e-02 -3.43288630e-02 -1.66091658e-02
